name: Smedium
pitch: Our Users would liket to make posts and respond to each other in a very streamlined way. They would like to respond to their friends and conversations with the information being easily available.
description: This will is a React based website that has an app bar and a MySQL database. The UX will be comprised of CSS using MaterialUI as a template. Pages will be controlled by using React Router DOM to for a streamlined experience and speed. Card components will be used to render posts and the project cards using the map funtion. Visitor information and comments can be logged on a server and sent to my email.

name: Lyric Jam
pitch: Our users would like the ability to listen to music while doing everyday activities and find that song later by using just one word. People are always looking for new forms of music and streaming companies make those songs more accessible than ever before.
description: Lyric Jam is a web application that uses JQuery, CSS, and HTML to allow users to search for songs, find lyrics for the song, and render the lyrics. It uses two API's, Songsterr and Lyriq, via AJAX requests to call objects of various song input by the user. Those objects are then rendered on the frontend

name: Employee Tracker
pitch: Often companies expand and must hire employees to do different functions. Our users would like an application for creating, tracking and assigning new employees titles. Employees will be given a specific ID for being recalled in later use and all entries will be stored to a backend server.
description: This application uses a Node frameork with Javascript for the underlying instructional code and SQL for the server. By starting app.js in node the user is Inquired if they would like to enter the database and complete tasks. Questions are asked by requiring the Inquire dependency. Once the user has made their inputs, their input is pushed to the backend server.

name: Portfolio One
pitch: Needing a functional website that displays my comprehension of market technologies and languages like React and CSS. Has to display completed projects that convey experience along with best practices. Allows prospective employers and collaborators an organized platform to contact me and see my work.
description: This will be a React based website that has three pages to show Projects, information About Me, and ways for people to Contact Me. I am using React Router DOM to organize the pages. A card component is rendering the project cards using the map funtion. Visitor information and comments can be logged on a server and sent to my email.

name: Employee Summary
pitch: Often companies expand and must hire employees to do different functions. Our users would like an application for creating, tracking and assigning new employees titles. Employees will be given a specific ID for being recalled in later use and all entries will be stored to a backend server.

name: Day Planner
pitch: Our users are highly effective people that want to maximize their time on a hourly basis. This Day Planner allows them to store tasks each day and see visual how their day is progressing.
description: This app generates a list of hour boxes using HTML and JQuery that can be used in order to save to-do items.
